{
  "text": ". We had previously shown [CITATION_1] that PdpB colocalizes with the bulk of the NADH oxidase activity, a marker for the inner membrane. The sucrose gradient fractions in which we found FopA and PdpB correspond well with the sucrose gradient densities found by Huntley and co-workers that contained outer-membrane proteins (1.18 g ml",
